Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.59,0:02:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this thing on?\NQuestions about, we had some questions
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.09,0:02:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,about the spiritual warrior.\NAs we evolve up through the various archetypes,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.25,0:02:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you see Jung talked about the archetypes.\NIn the beginning, we're the child.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.61,0:02:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual world is wondrous.\NWe go to the New Age festival
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.86,0:02:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're just blown away with it all.\NThen we get more serious, we get more aligned,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.09,0:02:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,we get more power, we give up the adolescent,\Nand we become dedicated to something.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.12,0:03:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of dedication arises the spiritual warrior.\NThe spiritual warrior, as it expresses itself
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.12,0:03:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in these classes, is extreme dedication\Nto the truth no matter what,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.06,0:03:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to die for the truth,\Nto give up all positionalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.34,0:03:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called devotional non-duality.\NAll right, so in the beginning,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.87,0:03:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual warrior starts from his solar plexus.\NHe knows what's right and he's willing to kill the infidel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.21,0:03:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He can kill the infidel.\NAnd many of the jihad people are in their spiritual warrior,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.88,0:03:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,energized by their spleen, unfortunately.\NTo kill the enemy out of hatred
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.87,0:03:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is a totally different karmic consequence\Nthan doing it out of one's dedication to principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.18,0:04:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So the more evolved spiritual warrior\Nis the archetype within you,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.09,0:04:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,which becomes dedicated to the truth.\NYou're a warrior to truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.47,0:04:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ was a warrior for truth.\NHe said, I brought a sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.97,0:04:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I did not bring you peace on earth,\Nbut peace in heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.71,0:04:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that correct?\NI did not bring you peace on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.80,0:04:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiots.\NThey deleted idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.99,0:04:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But I got the original and it said idiots.\NTo have any impact on mankind, you gotta be real.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.42,0:04:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You gotta know where mankind is living.\NSpeak to where we all live, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.56,0:04:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We all live where it's real, you know?\NWe talk from the intellect and spot all this fancy stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.66,0:04:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but where we live is the real.\NAnd on a certain level, everybody knows the real.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.06,0:04:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We discovered, for instance, which,\Nwell, that's this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.01,0:05:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to shock you with that one this morning.\NOh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.75,0:05:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we don't want to shock you with that one, no.\NAll right, then the warrior,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.60,0:05:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,he comes up out of the solar plexus\Nand stops being confrontational,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.37,0:05:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and he moves into his heart.\NSo you have the,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.14,0:05:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the warrior who also has a heart.\NThat pretty much represents the U.S. position right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.05,0:05:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Although it's a very ferocious and fearsome\Nand very powerful warrior, it also has a heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.50,0:05:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Right behind the guns is the food for the populace.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.64,0:05:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Who ever heard of a warrior doing that?\NDragging a wagon load of grub for the,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.72,0:05:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,for the evil ones out there, you know?\NNo, so America has more evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.18,0:05:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It has a heart about the whole thing,\Nand then he begins to speak of the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.81,0:06:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the warrior moves from warrior to a higher level,\Nbecause the archetype of the warrior
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.49,0:06:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is not the highest of evolution.\NBut that is the phase of the warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.75,0:06:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the warrior can also be,\Nthe downside of the warrior is the denouncer
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.93,0:06:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and the polarizer, you see?\NI said, once you speak for the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.19,0:06:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that's different than demeaning.\NThose who disagree with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.67,0:06:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So to vilify the president because you disagree with him\Nis not integrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.74,0:06:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,To say you disagree with him, that is integrous.\NBut to vilify him is a fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.47,0:06:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't vilify Bin Laden.\NI don't vilify Saddam Hussein.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.29,0:06:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,These are people that are run by energies\Nof which they have no awareness whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.94,0:06:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They have no awareness of what is running them.\NTherefore, intrinsically, everyone is innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.50,0:07:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What enables you to face the truth, you know, is, you know,\Nthe downside of things is the devotion to the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.91,0:07:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because the fastest way to God is through truth,\Nthe fast way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.58,0:07:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,One has to be devoted, so devotion brings in the heart.\NSo the Zen-like exactitude
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.74,0:07:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,is because of the devotion to God and truth.\NUnderstand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.33,0:07:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It can look ferocious.\NIt is ferocious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.38,0:07:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an enormous compassion then.\NOut of compassion, one can see the downside,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.44,0:07:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the mistaken side of the kamikaze pilot or the shoe bomber.\NThe shoe bomber, God bless him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.92,0:08:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Like the idiot child, you know.\NHe's doing his bit for the cause,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.82,0:08:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,getting on a plane with his shoes loaded with bombs.\NOh, God bless it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.58,0:08:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.89,0:08:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason that you have to take surgical action quickly,\Nyou know, talking as a pragmatist,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.43,0:08:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,after all, I'm a physician,\Nand I see things as a physician sees things,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.69,0:08:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the dangers to the world have become more,\Nthe dangers to the world are more than they ever were
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.85,0:08:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,because of amplification.\NBecause of amplification, a mad dog who used to be a weirdo
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.10,0:08:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that lived out in a trailer camp someplace and he looked weird,\Nand when he came to town, everybody thought he was a weirdo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.35,0:09:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Nowadays, he has access to enormously powerful weapons,\Nnot just a little harmless weirdo anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.36,0:09:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The deviant politics that comes through\Nthrough philosophical distortion used to be some guy ranting
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.16,0:09:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and raving in the bar and you all figured he's a local nut.\NNo, now he's on international television and he's talking
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.90,0:09:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to six million people at a time.\NTherefore, it is now far more important to detect,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.42,0:09:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,falsehood early in the game, early in the game.\NAnd that's one of the things that propelled, I'm sure,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.86,0:09:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,our administration to take action is because the capacity to deal\Nin nuclear weapons is so enormously powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.30,0:09:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to huge numbers of people.\NYou can't just fool around with these people anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.71,0:09:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't just say he's a local nut.\NWe'll just ignore him because he's carrying bombs
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.73,0:10:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's carrying nuclear weapons.\NAnd you can't just say, well, he's a local nut.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.10,0:10:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't just say he's a local nut.\NYou can't just dismiss the purveyors of falsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.89,0:10:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as harmless nuts who are carried away by mistaken enthusiasms\Nbecause they're influencing the opinion of millions of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.79,0:10:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So amplification then means that falsehood\Nin a way is more dangerous than it ever was.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.99,0:10:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Falsehood is more dangerous than it ever was.\NIt has always had a high price.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.07,0:10:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Denial is falsehood.\NYou say if you don't learn from history,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.17,0:10:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you're condemned to repeat it, huh?\NAnd that's why I use some historical examples
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.41,0:10:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're not so polarized about history\Nas we are about current events.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.05,0:10:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You can look at past history with a little more cool head\Nand not get your solar plexus all in an uproar
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.70,0:11:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,over current events.\NIf we looked, you know, my generation was World War II.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.83,0:11:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So after World War I, the espionage system\Nin the United States, the intelligence system,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.87,0:11:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,reported constantly to the Secretary of State.\NAnd every morning, the Secretary of State got a report
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.91,0:11:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,from the intelligence departments.\NAfter World War I, Secretary of State Stimson was appointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.85,0:11:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,When Stimson took office, they served him up on his first day\Nas Secretary of State with the intelligence report,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.25,0:11:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,which kept track of the Japanese especially.\NAnd he said these fateful words, gentlemen do not read other
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.10,0:11:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,gentleman's mail.\NThat cost us Pearl Harbor and millions of men
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.25,0:12:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because the intelligence was, I learned it from my,\NI learned it in grade school.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.47,0:12:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,My teacher said Japan with a swarming population like that\Nand lack of, what do you call it, rubber tires, oils,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.74,0:12:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,all that, what do you call that, whatever it is,\Nis going to have to expand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.79,0:12:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no choice.\NNobody ever thinks of controlling the population,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.73,0:12:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,by the way, in which you wouldn't have any shortage.\NBut anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.39,0:12:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It demands proclivity.\NYou know what, we have a constantly expanding population
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.84,0:12:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that is straining everything in every direction.\NSo Stimson played by the rules that we,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.22,0:12:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that the doctor and I did this morning.\NAnd he said, gentlemen do not read other gentleman's mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.22,0:12:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So intelligence reports to the State Department,\Nwhich were rife with all the intelligence
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.84,0:12:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of what Japan was preparing for, were completely ignored.\NAnd the results were Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.46,0:13:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,America is always being surprised, surprised.\NIt's always surprised by Pearl Harbor,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.51,0:13:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,surprised by the Bay of Pigs.\NSurprised, people are always being surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.94,0:13:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The only way you get to be surprised is to be stupid, right.\NYou have to have your head in the sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.77,0:13:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you're surprised when somebody gooses you .\NHe was surprised when kids...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.62,0:13:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, so beware of people that are surprised.\NYou won't live long on the streets ofines.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.62,0:13:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Change often.\NNew York City, being surprised, friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.42,0:13:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember walking at midnight\Non 10th Avenue,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.76,0:13:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and I heard the footsteps\Nbehind me. It's like one in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.24,0:13:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The sound of the footsteps,\NI knew what was on their mind, and what
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.72,0:13:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,they intended, and who they were,\Nwithout turning around. It would have been
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.20,0:13:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,a mistake to turn around.\NIf you don't have your antenna up, you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.34,0:14:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,survive. Okay,\Nto be virtuous and holier than thou, you've got
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.12,0:14:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to survive so you can get on TV and be\Nvirtuous and holier than thou.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.52,0:14:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So somebody's got to protect your butt while\Nyou're mouthing off, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.92,0:14:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You need a realist somewhere.\NAnd what's a realist? The realist
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.80,0:14:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,then is willing to\Naccept the downside of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.66,0:14:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,human life, because\Nhe's compassionate towards it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.13,0:14:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not compassionate,\Nthat means you're in a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.94,0:14:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,make-wrong, and if you're\Nin a make-wrong, you don't want to look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.69,0:14:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand what I'm saying? Compassion allows\Nyou to see that a lot of the people
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.57,0:14:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that walk the planet will\Nskin you alive, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.08,0:14:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They will. And if\Nyou love them enough, you realize
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.54,0:14:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that that is a fact. That's a fact.\NThey'll skin you alive. We'll get to more
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.66,0:14:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of that this afternoon. This afternoon we're going to talk about\Nbusiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.02,0:15:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Skin you alive.\NWhere naivete,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.94,0:15:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the downside of naivete\Ncosts everybody their life savings
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.94,0:15:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and retirement accounts.\NAll the old folks are working
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.84,0:15:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,at Walmarts right now.\NThe 401k
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.29,0:15:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,went west.\NSo we'll talk about that this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.55,0:15:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You see then that love\Nopens the door to the awareness of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.29,0:15:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,truth, because you don't have to take\Na positionality. You can
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.61,0:15:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,care for people\Nno matter what they might be,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.35,0:15:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,because you see that that's\Nonly where they've evolved to at this point
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.07,0:15:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of time. They've only\Nevolved to the point. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.28,0:15:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the people who are the mad bombers\Nare in the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.71,0:15:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,spleen of their\Nspiritual warrior. A dangerous
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.80,0:15:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,place to be. A very dangerous\Nplace to be. Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.95,0:16:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,they're very dangerous people.\NAnd to turn your
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.17,0:16:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,back to them and think that a prayer\Nvigil is going to stop and they ain't going to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.42,0:16:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So what can we all do as\Nindividuals? We can all be
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.35,0:16:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,champions of the truth. We can all come\Nout of denial. And we
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.34,0:16:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,can all evolve ourselves\Nspiritually as best we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.62,0:16:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we're talking about the spiritual.\NWe've talked about truth as
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.38,0:16:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,descriptive in form,\Nwhich is content, but
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.61,0:16:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that content is with an overall field\Ncalled context.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.12,0:16:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no such thing as a statement,\Na verifiable statement of truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.89,0:16:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that ignores context.\NThat's how all the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.48,0:16:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,fallacies that run this world arise.\NIt's true,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.66,0:16:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but not in this context, folks.\NNot in this context.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.92,0:17:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Our devotion to truth,\Nthen, because truth is the expression
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.85,0:17:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of God. God's expression\Nwithin the realm of human knowability
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.25,0:17:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is via truth\Nand via love,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.11,0:17:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,right? Via compassion,\Nvia understanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.53,0:17:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and benevolence.\NWe try to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.99,0:17:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,wage war in as benevolent\Na style as we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.30,0:17:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all you can say for the way.\NA lot different than a war we've all
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.19,0:17:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,lived through, or a lot of us older have lived through,\Nwhere it was done out of vengeance and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.02,0:17:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,hatred. That was a whole different energy.\NVengeance and hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.31,0:17:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not done out of vengeance and hatred,\Nalthough some of the aftermath of 9-11
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.18,0:17:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is vengeance and hatred.\NIt's pretty much
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.31,0:17:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,mellowed out.\NNo, 9-11 let loose
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.61,0:17:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the dogs of war.\N9-11 let loose the dogs of war
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.64,0:18:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and changed the game forever.\NNone of us are going to just hop
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.42,0:18:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,on a plane anymore.\NI think the rest of our lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.77,0:18:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to stand in line\Nand have our tick off our shoes
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.14,0:18:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, oh, that mad\Nshoe bomber. He really
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.23,0:18:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,screwed us up. I'm glad\NI wear Dr. Scholl's because
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.22,0:18:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I can zip them open, put my shoes back\Non like that. And the other kind
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.30,0:18:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of people have to do their shoelaces.\NThey're black shoes, of course, with shoelaces.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.70,0:18:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get to the black shoelaces\Npeople this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.00,0:18:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They're either businessmen or FBI. You know that right away.\NYeah, I never trust anybody with black
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.40,0:18:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,lace-up shoes, folks.\NThe afternoon good, one way or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.33,0:18:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so now\Nin this world, then, to be
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.90,0:19:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,mistaken is more dangerous than\Never. It's more dangerous
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.75,0:19:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,because the\Neffects are so amplified
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.25,0:19:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,by electronic communication,\Nby proliferations
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.92,0:19:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in science,\Nbomb making,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.42,0:19:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera, has become\Nanybody in his backyard
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.63,0:19:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,can brew up some\Ngerms that'll kill off millions of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.25,0:19:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,people. So,\Nyou can't allow
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.29,0:19:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,people to be as deviant as you\Nused to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.09,0:19:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The mad guy in the bar, you know,\Nhis only dangerousness
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.73,0:19:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,was he'd get behind the car and\Nkill somebody on the way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.53,0:19:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the mad person now can\Nwith a little chemistry
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.24,0:19:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,set, stir up enough germs\Nto kill half of the people in this
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.33,0:19:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,planet. So,\Nwe can't allow deviance
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.09,0:19:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and negativity to\Nreach the point of dangerousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.93,0:20:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We're too close to the ruptured\Nappendix now. You've got to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.25,0:20:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,operate a little earlier in the game.\NBetter to make a mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.78,0:20:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and take out a healthy appendix once in a\Nwhile than to lose
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.45,0:20:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a teenage girl.\NSo, the surgeon gets
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.63,0:20:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,criticized. Well, we looked at it\Nin pathology and there was nothing wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.63,0:20:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,with that appendix. It was really\Nmesenteric adenitis.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.81,0:20:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But at the time, it sure looked like\Nappendicitis. So, what's the guy going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.51,0:20:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, he takes a\Nrisk that he gets criticized
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.74,0:20:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and he has to go before\Nthe hospital board to explain
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.79,0:20:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,how come you took out\Na healthy appendix. Well, he didn't think
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.27,0:20:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a healthy appendix, but he didn't\Nwant to take a chance. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.08,0:20:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the margin of error now, in a way,\Nis less than it used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.54,0:20:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The margin of error. Everything moves\Nmuch faster because of the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.30,0:20:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is amplified.\NSo, error as well as truth
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.56,0:21:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,gets quickly amplified.\NBecause it's quickly amplified, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.35,0:21:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,our own spiritual work has a\Ngreater impact. And as
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.59,0:21:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,we mentioned before, when we were\Ntalking about going
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.50,0:21:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,from the linear to the non-linear, from\NNewtonian science
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.50,0:21:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to quantum mechanics\Nand beyond,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.65,0:21:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you saw that each\Nchoice that you make then
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.71,0:21:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,collapses the wave function, speaking\Nfrom the viewpoint of quantum mechanics,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.80,0:21:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and reinforces\Nthe field.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.07,0:21:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Reinforces the field.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.68,0:21:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore,\Nyour own integrity in
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.20,0:21:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,striving for truth raises\Nthe consciousness level of all of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.57,0:21:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind. And that which\Nmakes falsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.85,0:21:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,weaker instead of stronger\Nis the prevalence
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.94,0:21:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of the consciousness of mankind\Nin general.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.64,0:22:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness level now at\N207 is going to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.64,0:22:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,surface that which is negative.\NYou understand? As you move
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.51,0:22:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,from 190, which was non-integral,\Nto 180, which is non-integral,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.25,0:22:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to the non-integral, which is\Nnon-integral, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.80,0:22:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,non-integral, which is\Nnon-integral, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.93,0:22:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,non-integral, which is\Nnon-integral, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.16,0:22:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,non-integral.\NSo, I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.53,0:22:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to jump the story of\Nbusiness, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.53,0:22:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what I was taught, I\Nremember a sales guy who was trying
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.53,0:22:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to get me to sell peanut vending\Nmachines. Did I tell you my peanut
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.53,0:22:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,vending machine story?\NThat's really this afternoon's
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.53,0:22:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,story, but would you give me a\Nlittle preview?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.84,0:22:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I had 1,001 jobs, you know,\N1,001 jobs. People think they're
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.84,0:22:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,underpaid now. I worked as an\Nintern 100 hours a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.84,0:22:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's 400 hours a week.\NThat's 400 hours a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.84,0:22:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's 400 hours a week.\NThat's 400 hours a month for
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.84,0:22:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,$100 a month, so that's a\Nquarter an hour, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.84,0:22:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, in the summertime,\Nyou had to find a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.84,0:22:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, in the summertime, you\Nhad to find a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.80,0:22:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, in the summertime, you\Nhad to find a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.80,0:22:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So here was this ad to be a\Nsales representative.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.80,0:22:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So the job\NSo here was this ad to be a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.09,0:22:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,sales representative.\NSo the job was you work for
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.09,0:22:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,this sales guy.\NHe comes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.09,0:22:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He checks in a hotel.\NYou meet him in this hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.13,0:23:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He gives you the pitch.\NThe pitch is you get these
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.13,0:23:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,retired farmers\Nretirement money,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.13,0:23:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and you get them to invest in\Npeanut vending machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.13,0:23:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.27,0:23:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.88,0:23:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.88,0:23:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.88,0:23:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.88,0:23:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.88,0:23:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.88,0:23:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.88,0:23:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.51,0:23:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.51,0:23:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.51,0:23:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.51,0:23:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.16,0:23:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.16,0:23:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.50,0:23:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.67,0:23:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nfrom the viewpoint of honesty and integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.88,0:23:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I brought this up, and he said,\NI said, that's really not right to fool these guys
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.55,0:23:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,out of their retirement when you know\Nit's not going to be emptying every week or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.90,0:24:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, if you don't get their money, somebody else will.\NThere you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.68,0:24:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was the world of the 30s or 40s.\NI don't know what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.63,0:24:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the prevailing level of consciousness was 190.\NAnd at 190, business was business.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.71,0:24:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And ethics was ethics.\NAnd you don't miss the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.42,0:24:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't get their money, somebody will.\NThere you got the rationalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.81,0:24:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So nonintegrity survives by virtue of rationalization,\Nmaking it sound OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.40,0:24:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But truth cuts through that.\NSo my intuition told me that I really
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.81,0:24:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't have the heart to take people's retirement money.\NAt death's door, you're going to be reviewing your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.11,0:24:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'll be looking at all these poor old guys,\Nand I'll take the retirement money.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.51,0:24:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I really didn't want to look at that.\NSo people now that are dedicated to spiritual truth
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.83,0:25:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,have a great impact on the collective consciousness\Nof mankind, because it went from 190 to 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.04,0:25:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, 207 is a whole new ballgame.\NAt 207, nonintegrity begins to surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.44,0:25:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,like the good begins to drive out the bad.\NSo at 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.24,0:25:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how we conduct a war, even in a world that's at 207,\Nalthough the US is at 431.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.53,0:25:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We try to, as ambiguous as it may sound,\Nwe try to conduct an ethical war.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.71,0:25:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,An ethical war.\NAs ethical as you can make it, surgical precision.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.79,0:25:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Try to be benevolent at the same time.\NSnare the Komodo dragon before it kills any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.07,0:25:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is the moral.\NYou might say the moral predicament of the US.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.84,0:26:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And the way I see the US handling it at the present time\Nis best it can with an unpleasant condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.05,0:26:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, has anybody got any questions about war and peace,\Nseeing as we just straightened out Sun Tzu, who
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.28,0:26:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,wrote The Art of War?\NThe classic is The Art of War by Sun Tzu.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.51,0:26:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The Art of War.\NIt's an art form.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.18,0:26:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's.\NI like this title, The Art of War.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.34,0:26:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The Art of War.\NYou see how it looks at it as a game board.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.30,0:26:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody had a question?\NWe'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.59,0:26:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a few more minutes.\NAnd then we're going to have lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.96,0:26:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And then this afternoon, I want to do business, science,\Nand many other areas of human life.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.33,0:26:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You can stand up and speak, please.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.93,0:27:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.\NThey're both the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.42,0:27:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a quality.\NYou see, from here down, what you're really talking about,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.66,0:27:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,are negative energies, which classically, theologically,\Nreligiously, spiritually, have been called either Luciferic
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.14,0:27:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,or Satanic or demonic.\NThis is the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.57,0:27:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, non-truth, then.\NAnd those are just different qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.29,0:27:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Satanic has been, it takes two forms.\NOur society is attacked by both ends, by the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.02,0:27:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The Satanic takes the form of bloodshed.\NKilling, murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.67,0:27:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The ultimate Satanic energy is the serial child killer,\Nwho calibrates around seven, by the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.76,0:27:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The pornographic addict child killer\Ncalibrates probably the lowest of all, around seven
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.10,0:28:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,or something.\NIt has to do with cruelty, savagery.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.15,0:28:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw it in Nanking in the 30s.\N30,000 innocent civilians slaughtered, raped, murdered,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.05,0:28:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera, et cetera.\NIt preys upon the weak and the innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.73,0:28:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, oh, while we're talking about ethics,\Nit is unethical and non-integrous to tempt people
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.18,0:28:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,with weakness.\NTo purposely place temptation in front of people,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.95,0:28:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you must handle the karmic consequences.\NIf you have a new maid to clean your house,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.84,0:28:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and you leave a pile of cash sitting out there,\Nwho is the perpetrator?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.59,0:28:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And who is the victim?\NYou're the perpetrator.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.94,0:28:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause you're provoking human weakness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.48,0:28:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Lead us not into temptation.\NSo to lead people into temptation.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.90,0:29:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So weakness leads people into temptation.\NTo be in denial makes you a choice, plump little victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.43,0:29:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I hadn't had paranoid alertness,\NI would have got mugged on 10th Avenue that night,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.25,0:29:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and many other times in New York City.\NNo, you can't be into denial, because that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.85,0:29:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,makes you the provocateur by virtue of the temptation\Nand attraction of weakness.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.75,0:29:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the predator-prey response.\NThat's why weakness does not work
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.72,0:29:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in international politics.\NWeakness just pulls forth the predator.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.57,0:29:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He just can't resist the fact that you've\Ngot all that money, all that vulnerability sitting there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.33,0:29:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have to take moral responsibility\Nthat you tempted the predator.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.92,0:29:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So the victim doesn't stop being victim\Nuntil the victim takes responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.96,0:30:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,for the part they play.\NIf you want to go jogging at midnight in Central Park,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.22,0:30:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to take responsibility that you're\Na luscious little victim that is going
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.33,0:30:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to be beyond the self-control of half-drunken or intoxicated\Npeople with no sense of honor or ethics.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.50,0:30:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to get raped no matter what.\NYou keep doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.90,0:30:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If not tonight, tomorrow night, sooner or later.\NSo we see that weakness then has a moral downside to it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.51,0:30:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and that you are tempting those who are weak.\NNow, how do we know they're weak?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.75,0:30:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they calibrate below 200.\NYou're tempting 78% of the population.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.25,0:30:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Vulnerability and weakness tempts 78% of the population.\N78% of the population.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.55,0:30:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd the rest of the population is not
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.16,0:30:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,interested in peace, ethics, or honor,\Nunless it's a pop political slogan.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.35,0:31:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like the peace movement is not about peace.\NIt's about politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.01,0:31:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, it's using peace as a slogan.\NAnd therefore, it denigrates the true meaning of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.50,0:31:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that which is peaceful does not denigrate,\Ndoes not marginalize people.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.22,0:31:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is contentious.\NContentious is not peaceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.01,0:31:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace does not come out of contention.\NWhat comes out of contention?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.74,0:31:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,War comes out of contention.\NSo if you make peace contentious, you're declaring war.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.56,0:31:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,To declare war in the name of peace is lucifer.\NYou see how you take what sounds like truth
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.20,0:31:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and you turn it into its opposite.\NYou polarize the people in a contentious war of ideology,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.83,0:31:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,power politics.\NAnd it deviates.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.42,0:31:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And it deviates.\NAnd it deviates.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.67,0:31:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And it deviates.\NAnd it deviates.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.97,0:31:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And it deviates.\NAnd it deviates.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.13,0:31:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And it deviates.\NAnd it divides people.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.43,0:32:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That which divides people into war and camps\Ndoes not represent peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.65,0:32:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that which is peace unites people.\NSo 78% of the population, then, is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.19,0:32:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,run by what we call dark energies.\NThose on the right-hand side are called, in politics,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.83,0:32:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,keep the calibrated level up.\NIn politics, we call the far right fascist.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.07,0:32:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The far right is fascist.\NThe far left is Marxist.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.38,0:32:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The far right is fascist.\NThe far right is cruel, fascistic, and dictatorial.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.92,0:32:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's savage.\NIt's merciless.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.59,0:32:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's without compassion.\NIn China right now, to even voice certain things
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.01,0:32:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,gets you not only arrested, but executed.\NExecuted.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.29,0:32:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The same as in Arabic countries.\NEven do or say certain things brings
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.55,0:33:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,automatic, instant execution.\NForget about trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.41,0:33:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget about lawyers, martial law.\NIt precludes all those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.73,0:33:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So the far right is fascistic, sadistic.\NAnother aspect of the satanic, which
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.24,0:33:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,may not look the same to you, has\Nto do with sexuality, sexual perversion, sexual obsession,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.00,0:33:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,drugs, the kind of music put out by certain groups.\NKick your pregnant wife in the belly, hate rock, and obscenity.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.50,0:33:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Great names celebrated by the media are overtly profane,\Novertly sacrilegious, overtly, overtly attack
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.24,0:34:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is sacred, that which is divine, that which is holy.\NEspecially innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.99,0:34:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That which attracts the satanic is innocence.\NInnocence in our culture is youth.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.53,0:34:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it's very easy to program youth with programs that respect\Nor decency, is being white, is being uncool.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.01,0:34:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The contempt for that which is holy and sacred comes out of the satanic.\NSo we have the satanic attacking our culture via the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.23,0:34:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The main avenue of the satanic attack is via the media,\Nin which many of these musical things calibrate 70 or 80.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.44,0:34:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, this week, I was at a concert.\NI was at a concert.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.34,0:34:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The media announced a new video game.\NIt's called a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.96,0:35:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Drop your guard, folks.\NIt's just a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.21,0:35:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called Postal 2.\NPostal 2 is worse than Postal 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.28,0:35:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Postal 2 and 1 is worse than, what's that name, auto something?\NHuh? Grand Theft Auto, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.73,0:35:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Grand Theft Auto is bad enough, but Postal is trying to win the game of seeing\Nhow depraved can you get.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.78,0:35:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see what Postal calibrates.\NWe have permission to calibrate in front of this audience, Postal, a video game, which is over 30.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.05,0:35:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there is an innocent game, which is programming your unconscious at a calibrated level of 30,\Nwhich is contempt for all that is decent, holy, or integrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.03,0:36:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Savagery at its extreme.\NThat's satanic.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.36,0:36:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have satanic in the political realm.\NIt's fascism.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.28,0:36:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We have it in the realm of the lower, what do we call it, the bottom of the barrel of society.\NDrug addiction, savagery, murder, pimps, prostitutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.53,0:36:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Pimps don't do very well calibration-wise either.\NThey do about 30.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.88,0:36:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I said 30?\NYeah, 30.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.67,0:36:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Said sadism.\NThey like to beat up the girls, you know, and savage them, terrify them, stab them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.40,0:36:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They get out of line.\NSo you got six girls in your stable, one gets out, you cut her eyes out.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.75,0:36:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That scares the crap out of everybody on the street.\NAnd after that, they do what the hell you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.82,0:37:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, I once treated a pimp back in the East, and I know the extent to which they go.\NHe would come in and say, God, I'm exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.09,0:37:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You think beating up girls all night is easy?\NYou should try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.69,0:37:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He's trying for my sympathy.\NThese girls have forced him, forced him, they forced him to do this, is the way he looks at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.15,0:37:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,She misbehaved.\NWhat else could I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.82,0:37:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, can't keep this.\NAll right, so that's satanic.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.46,0:37:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the Luciferic is something different.\NSo the satanic can take you all the way down to seven, the serial child killer calibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.05,0:37:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,at seven.\NThey're usually possessed from lower astral domains, and really not in a certain way,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.76,0:37:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,not really responsible.\NAll right, the Luciferic is something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.00,0:37:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The Luciferic, what is Lucifer?\NLucifer's sin was pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.38,0:38:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Luciferic stands for the denial of the sovereignty of God, therefore it is the\Nultimate of arrogance and pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.21,0:38:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Luciferic is at 190.\NIn our society, the far left calibrates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.59,0:38:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The refusal to accept divinity.\NSo that particular energy wants to wipe God out.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.76,0:38:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,In human society, and turn it into a secular society.\NWell, the reason our society calibrates as high as it does is the Constitution of the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.57,0:38:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,United States is over 700, because the rights and equality of all men are a result of the\Nacknowledgement of the divinity of our creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.05,0:38:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason we're equal is because we are created that way by God.\NThat's what makes 720.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.23,0:38:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The Constitution of the United States is the highest.\NSo it's over 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.67,0:38:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All right?\Nhighest of any government on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.19,0:39:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Luciferic would like to remove any acknowledgement of God because Lucifer's pride\Nwas he did not want to acknowledge that there was any power greater than him.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.84,0:39:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Luciferic, to begin with, hates God and wants to remove any reminder of God in\Nevery place in America.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.13,0:39:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember when Madeleine Murray wanted God removed as, I think it was prayer in the school,\Nisn't that prayer in the school?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.90,0:39:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,She became the most hated, despised woman in America, and I saw a documentary on her\Nsubsequent life, and it was abysmal, down to the trailer park, then down to degradation,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.78,0:39:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,then down to murder and suicide in the family, and then family murder.\NIt was downhill.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.59,0:39:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, to say that, to destroy God is a different intention.\NSo the energy of a thing comes out of its spiritual intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.84,0:40:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,To destroy God is to restore God.\NI refuse to acknowledge the source of one's own existence, which is a Luciferic error.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.25,0:40:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,To arrive at that, you have to do a great deal of alteration of philosophy, and so the\Nphilosophical and ethical basis upon which these things rest are always gross distortions.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.28,0:40:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And one way you can tell they're gross distortions is because they're contentious.\NOne way they're contentious.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.92,0:40:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,One way they're contentious is they demean the opposite view.\NYou see, in a debating class, each person presents his side, and he presents his side.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.98,0:40:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In that which is contentious, you don't present your side, you attack their side, which is\Na different approach altogether, you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.07,0:40:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't care whether anybody agrees with anything I say whatsoever.\NWhy should I care?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.00,0:40:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would you want to influence other people?\NHave a parade?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.53,0:41:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Make speeches on TV?\NWhy would anybody want to control anybody else, control what they think, control what
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.34,0:41:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,they believe?\NI'm sure these people believe that what they're doing is for God when they blow up a whole
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.78,0:41:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,airplane full of innocent passengers.\NThey probably felt virtuous as they killed 3,000 in the Twin Towers.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.96,0:41:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Pearl Harbor only killed 2,000 in 2400.\NPearl Harbor only killed 2,400.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.80,0:41:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was a military target.\NThe Twin Towers killed 3,000, not military target, innocent civilians, blown up without
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.21,0:42:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,any chance to prepare for death, no confession, no absolution, no nothing, out of body, 3,000\Ninnocent civilians.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.76,0:42:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't see any peace parades after Pearl Harbor, nobody told me it was unintegrated\Nto counter attack Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.50,0:42:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't see any peace parades after Pearl Harbor.\NA littleTIN.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.48,0:42:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Why no?\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.67,0:42:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if we calibrate the level of truth of that particular distortion of truth, we see\Nit calibrates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.63,0:42:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,190 is putting one's own ego above the reality of God.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.44,0:42:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the reason it's below 200 is because it's a denial of truth.\NSo, the left end is characterized, that...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.73,0:42:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucifer is characterized by arrogance.\NArrogance and remorse.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.15,0:42:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,replacing facts with opinions and by distorting the truth,\Ndistorting the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.50,0:43:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the difference between Luciferic and Satanic.\NOne form of the Luciferic is to distort truth
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.26,0:43:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you cannot tell good from evil.\NIn our society, many people cannot tell good from evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.15,0:43:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,One side of conflict is demonic, calibrates at 70,\Nand frankly, after it's juiced you, it will kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.75,0:43:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So people parade to the defense of that energy.\NLenin said they're useful idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.55,0:43:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Lenin was the one that introduced terrorism\Nas a legitimate way of achieving one's goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.48,0:43:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It was Lenin that popularized terrorism\Nin the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.73,0:44:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who supported his position,\Nhe called them useful idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.13,0:44:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And after the revolution,\Nthey're the first ones to be extinguished.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.13,0:44:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The first ones you're gonna execute after the revolution\Nbecause if a person is not aligned with their own origins,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.19,0:44:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,if they don't respect their father and mother,\Ntheir own culture,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.11,0:44:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they turn against their own.\NIf they turn against their own, you can't trust them.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.28,0:44:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So after the revolution, you kill them all.\NThe first people extinguished after a revolution
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.03,0:44:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,are the revolutionaries.\NThe intellectual revolutionaries,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.65,0:44:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,who sell out their own integrity\Nfor the gain of being superior.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.51,0:44:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So Stalin said he called them useful idiots,\Nand after the revolution, they're all shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.59,0:44:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So they don't bring about freedom,\Nthey bring about their own execution.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.21,0:45:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The devotion to the truth, then,\Nmeans the willingness to look at some painful facts of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.36,0:45:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Painful facts of life.\NThe ostrich head in the sand,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.50,0:45:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is a wimp. The wimp is unable to look at the downside of human life.\NGentlemen don't read other gentleman's mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.59,0:45:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't other gentleman's mail he was reading.\NThe Japanese were planning Pearl Harbor
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.71,0:45:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and the destruction of the United States influence\Nin the entire Pacific.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.71,0:45:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And kill as many Americans as possible.\NSo you see in the interacting balance of power
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.75,0:45:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,how these levels of consciousness\Nwhich tend to manifest in various places geographically
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.75,0:45:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,force certain moves.\NYou see how the victim forces the perpetrator.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.07,0:46:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The victim forces the perpetrator\Nto take action against them.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.78,0:46:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Suicide by police is the name of the game.\NThe second atomic bomb
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.80,0:46:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,after World War II\Nwas forced upon themselves by Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.36,0:46:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't get the implication\Nthat a second atomic bomb
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.78,0:46:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that doesn't stop you.\NThey forced a second atomic bomb
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.01,0:46:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,before they got it.\NIs that stupid or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.48,0:46:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The two atomic bombs they get\Nthat the war is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.48,0:46:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We have met our master.\NHe was correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.03,0:46:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We awaken the sleeping giant.\NOnce you wake up the sleeping giant
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.03,0:46:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the game is over.\NSo we looked at this morning at the realities of war and peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.30,0:46:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We use consciousness research to find,\Nto get to the core
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.30,0:47:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of what is the truth of these things.\NOne way to get to the truth of it is
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.01,0:47:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,being personal about it.\NDon't have any position about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.01,0:47:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care if this side is right or that side is right.\NIt's immaterial.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.03,0:47:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Because where I live all that is just nonsensical drama anyway.\NIt's all the games of the ego out there
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.03,0:47:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm not the ego and neither are you.\NSo who cares about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.55,0:47:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody wants to kill each other.\NLet them.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.55,0:47:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should you interfere?\NWhy should you interfere?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.09,0:47:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,People get a wallop\Nby killing themselves and others.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.44,0:47:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a game.\NThat's going to be difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.03,0:47:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know that it's possible.\NI don't know that it's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.84,0:47:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We have historically, I always go back to history\Nbecause if you don't learn from history
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.84,0:48:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to repeat it.\NThe difficulty with the Russians of course
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.84,0:48:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is they had no knowledge of ways of freedom.\NHow to hold title to a house.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.84,0:48:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you buy a house?\NHow do you open a bank account?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.84,0:48:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean checking account?\NWhat do you mean mortgage?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.84,0:48:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They had no idea what we're even talking about.\NIt made no sense to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.76,0:48:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So generally what you have then\Nwhen you remove a fascist regime
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.76,0:48:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is you have a period of political unrest\Nand instability and chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.76,0:48:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the warring factions come out again.\NThe communists will try to take over.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.21,0:48:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The fascists will try to take over.\NThe different religious factions
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.21,0:48:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,will try to take over.\NAnd I expect chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.21,0:48:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I imagine it's going to be a mess for a long time.\NBecause our idea of living with those who differ from us
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.40,0:48:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,don't forget it took us hundreds of years.\NAmerica was old by the time
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.59,0:48:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we even settled blacks and whites, right?\NWhen I was young
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.71,0:49:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the blacks had their own bathrooms and bus stations.\NAnd I just as a kid thought that's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.71,0:49:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that's the way it is\Nbecause black people are poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.94,0:49:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't think it was because they were black.\NI just thought in terms of black and white.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.94,0:49:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I just thought that they must be poor\Nthat they don't have washstands that work.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.94,0:49:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The toilets don't work.\NAnd the filling station was dilapidated
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.11,0:49:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that they used.\NAnd then the white man's
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.11,0:49:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,either was all about money, you know?\NSo it took us hundreds of years
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.30,0:49:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to even settle that simple an issue.\NAnd the Catholics and the Protestants
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.30,0:49:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,warred for thousands of, you know,\Na thousand years, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.30,0:49:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They're still at it in Northern Ireland.\NSo even a society
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.88,0:49:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,at 400, you know,\Nit takes it hundreds of years to settle out.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.03,0:49:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So I would guess Iraq will\Nsettle out in four or five hundred years.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.03,0:49:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, those factions have been at it\Nfor thousands of years already.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.09,0:49:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They all hate each other with a vengeance.\NThey're all coming out of the spleen.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.09,0:50:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the Palestinians kill a busload of kids\Nand then the Israelis
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.15,0:50:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,kill a busload of pregnant mothers.\NYou know, the more pathetic the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.15,0:50:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to answer that\Nand then we're going to have to break for lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.94,0:50:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NI'll answer it this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.46,0:50:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,From my general knowledge\Nof the evolution of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.78,0:50:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,which I went into somewhat in the last book\Nand which we'll go into more in the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.78,0:50:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution of consciousness\Nsince the beginning of time
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.78,0:50:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,has been an upward trajectory.\NAnd at a certain point,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.94,0:50:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you might say the accumulated positive karma,\Nthe karmic merit
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.15,0:50:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of mankind has earned it\Nthe right to go over 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.57,0:51:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Karmic merit has evolved\Nbecause, you see, at the time of Buddha,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.57,0:51:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of consciousness of mankind was 90.\NAt the time of Jesus Christ, it was 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.76,0:51:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,By the 1600s, it was up to 185,\Nand then you saw it at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.86,0:51:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I came into this world,\N190 ran everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.32,0:51:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And then suddenly in the late 80s,\Nit jumps to 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.32,0:51:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, what's significant about that,\Nis that you're on the other side of the,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.40,0:51:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you're on the other side.\NSo on a ship,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.98,0:51:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, I steer the ship\Na half a degree off,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.98,0:51:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and the compass doesn't seem like much.\NBut a half a degree
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.98,0:51:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,after a day or two of sailing\Nacross the Pacific Ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.98,0:51:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you're a couple hundred miles off.\NSo just a few degrees
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.36,0:51:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,makes the difference between success and failure.\NSo, as I say, the reason you see
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.36,0:51:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of non-integrity surfacing in Ron,\Nand we're going to get to that this afternoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.36,0:52:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,big corporations falling,\Ncongressmen being nailed
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.42,0:52:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,for dishonesty and stuff,\Nis because 207 will not tolerate
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.42,0:52:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that degree of non-integrity.\N190, we said, business is business.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.42,0:52:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Steal a little, just don't make it too much.\NAnd 207 now calls for a different action.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.51,0:52:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember I had a housekeeper many years ago,\Nand she used to do the shopping for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.00,0:52:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and I would then later check with the grocery,\Nand she padded the bill 10%.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.86,0:52:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And I figured, so it's 10%.\NI didn't fire her.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.86,0:52:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,She padded it a little bit.\NI know she's running about 10%.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.86,0:52:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,She'd tell me the groceries were $22,\Nand actually they're only $18.90.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.86,0:52:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So I figured, she's only stealing 10%,\Nso I never said anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.86,0:53:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you'd feel you have to say something.\NYou can't just sweep everything under the rug anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.15,0:53:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now integrity would say,\NI'd have to tell her,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.30,0:53:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,listen, you're going 10% on top of the bill.\NNow, I may negotiate with her and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.15,0:53:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,look, if you want a 10% raise,\Ntell me, and I'll give you 10% more.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.15,0:53:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've got to get myself out of integrity,\Nand I'm going to be non-integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.15,0:53:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,if I don't call her on it.\NAt 190, I'd say, look,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.36,0:53:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,she's only stealing 10%.\NGood.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.36,0:53:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Good housekeepers are hard to get.\NBut now I've got to live with that
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.36,0:53:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because I realize there's a karmic consequence\Nto saying okay to non-integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.36,0:53:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, okay.\NSo it's a new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.53,0:53:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So eat well because this afternoon\Nwe're going to hit business.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.53,0:54:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,A difficult morning.\NOnly a couple of deaths along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.88,0:54:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody got outraged with what I had to say\Nand left enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.98,0:54:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So I consider that a great blessing.\NTo try and contextualize compassion
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.63,0:54:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for all positions.\NTo be compassionate for your enemy
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.36,0:54:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,who is walking under some kind of an understanding\Njust as you're walking under some kind of an understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.67,0:54:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm sure on some other plane,\Nsome other day, we'll all laugh about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.15,0:54:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think I've shared with you\Nthe laughter I had with the fellow
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.86,0:54:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that I skewered with a sword and he skewered me.\NHe did it for Allah and I did it for God.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.09,0:55:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And I mean, we killed each other good, too.\NI remember exactly both experts.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.28,0:55:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And boy, did I kill him.\NAnd did he ever kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.28,0:55:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We were just fantastic.\NAt the zen of weaponry.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.50,0:55:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And we both went out of body and got hysterical.\NI killed him for Jesus and he killed me for Allah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.88,0:55:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it was the funniest thing.\NAnd in that moment, you transcend your warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.03,0:55:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand the warrior?\NWe transcended the warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.03,0:55:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was willing to die for God, Jesus.\NI died for Jesus and he did it for Allah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.46,0:55:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So I've respected the enemy ever since\Nbecause he's just like I am
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.96,0:55:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in some different level of\Nkarmic working out.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.23,0:55:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, this is the karmic theater of\Nthe universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.38,0:55:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How can there be such a variation?\NAnd shouldn't the world be different than it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.38,0:56:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We can do without the garbage cans.\NI get carried away with their beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.90,0:56:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I can't remember what I'm saying.\NWhere did that come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.44,0:56:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.\NIt's in the lower right.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.78,0:56:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Tom Lincoln sent us that.\NOkay, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.96,0:56:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is perfect.\NThe world is perfect as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.67,0:56:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no intention to change it\Nbecause if this is supposed to be
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.80,0:56:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the perfect school for all of us to evolve,\Nto undo bad karma, achieve new karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.80,0:56:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,then we need the whole panorama\Nfrom the very worst to the very top.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.46,0:56:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what our world represents.\NIf it's the perfect world, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.09,0:56:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,for what it is, purgatorial in nature,\Nwhere else would you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.13,0:57:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't for this world,\Nwhere would I have killed that guy for Jesus?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.44,0:57:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And where would he have killed me for Allah?\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.44,0:57:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to be someplace that tolerates this craziness.\NThis world rewards you for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.38,0:57:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So we both went out here, went out as heroes.\NWe were both heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.38,0:57:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we transcended the warrior at that time.\NSo each of those archetypes then represent
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.63,0:57:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,evolutionary steps in the evolution of consciousness.\NAt one point, I didn't mean to say
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.05,0:57:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the ultimate, but it's not.\NBut it's just the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.05,0:57:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way it is.\NI've tried to try to make clear this morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.71,0:57:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and it'll carry over till this afternoon,\Nis the difference between authority and authoritarian.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.71,0:57:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a purposeful misinterpretation of authority\Nas authoritarian to justify demonizing authority
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.15,0:58:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,by purposely distorting it as authoritarian.\Ndictatorial there is such a thing as true authority by virtue of the nature
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.92,0:58:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which it is it is intrinsically the authority the authority and what it\Nis to be the cat is my cat and anything I say is not coming from the authority
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.71,0:58:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,because the the authority of being that which you are psychoanalytically I always\Nviewed the fact your relationship at least amongst men the relationship you
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.90,0:58:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,had with your father will pretty much set your political position later on if\Nyour father was cruel unloving at Sarah you will hate authority and be therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.26,0:58:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,against all that stands for authority big business institutions the government\Nand whatever please hmm view all authority as evil and get out on a
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.01,0:59:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,bandstand and parade against authority and so authoritarian is the\Nabuse of power. Authority is the true nature of power because truth is power
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.57,0:59:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and the true true authority comes from integrity. So if you had a father who was\Nfair and yet firm but loved you at the same time, you will view authority as
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.19,0:59:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,both friendly and to be respected. Patriotism is the respect, the love, the\Nacknowledgement. At the same time, the limitation of society is accepted and
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.11,0:59:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the police are seen as somebody who will protect you, not just, you know, somebody\Nwho in an authoritarian, abusive way unleashes the dogs
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.48,1:00:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,against innocent victims, you see, because the victims are not innocent. You don't\Nget the police dogs released on you because you were having a peace vigil.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.28,1:00:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Takes a lot of rock throwing before you know it.\NYou get the police to get out the water hoses, etc. So you see the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.23,1:00:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,provocation, and you see that especially in the Middle East, where one side\Nprovokes the other into action so they can then blame the other and hold the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.21,1:00:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,innocent baby in her arms as the mother cries, which they keep a whole bunch of\Nthose videos on hand at all times. We played first on one side and then the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.82,1:00:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,other, you see. So that's the victimization of the public by the abuse\Nof the power of communication of the media to
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.30,1:00:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,purpose.\NThis is the, bring up maudlin distortions of the reality. So how you view authority
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.36,1:00:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,then? If you hate authority because your father was cruel and authoritarian, or\Nwhether your father was benign and loving and supportive at the same time demanded
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.55,1:01:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that you finish your homework. So positionality about authority then has\Nsomething to do with many, many things, one of them being childhood experience of
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.28,1:01:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,how you were parented.\NIf your mother and father were unfeeling and cruel, then you'd be very hostile to
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.48,1:01:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it. So our host thought a lot of people who protest authority, even in its\Nlegitimate form, probably had a very bad relationship with their fathers, you know
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.84,1:01:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,what I'm saying? So there's many psychological, psychoanalytic, as well as the nature of\Nthe ego itself, which tends to positionalize us and get into right and
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.59,1:01:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,wrong. So this afternoon we're going to talk about business. Let's have business up here.\NThey say if you got through war, business will be a snap.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.05,1:02:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If this morning didn't blow you out, you'd probably be okay. Now this looks pretty, is\Nthat readable? All right. Because of its importance to our culture, war and peace has to do with
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.30,1:02:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,staying alive. Now that you're staying alive, how do you survive? So survival then takes\Nus into the world of a job, business, commerce, money, abundance, abundance, abundance, abundance,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.07,1:02:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,abundance, abundance, abundance, abundance, abundance, abundance, abundance, abundance,\Nabundance, and all of those then are experienced depending on one's level of
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.82,1:02:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness. So we want to talk about success. There's many workshops on\Nsuccess and making money, and I could never afford to go to one of them when I
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.84,1:02:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,was younger. It's 350 for the weekend, then I figure, you always say you stay\Npoor. Okay, that's great. That's all right. Everybody can cock their head a little
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.84,1:02:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,bit. We can tell who's paying attention.\NWho's paying attention? Who ain't? That's fine. That's fine. That's good. That's good.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.40,1:03:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. That's good. All right. So the demonization, the vilification of business then comes from\Nthe same source as that which denigrates the United States and its presidency and the flag
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.94,1:03:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and God and the Constitution and all that.\NBecause business is seen as a source of power, it's hated and stigmatized, and every time,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.92,1:03:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,there's an international business conference. They parade up and down the sidewalk with\Nsigns. They hate business, and they hate big business. So I always get a kick out of
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.07,1:03:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,these guys. Here he's got glasses on made by some business. He's got a shirt on made\Nby some business. He's got pants on made by some business. His shoes were made by some
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.21,1:04:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,business. His watch, he's looking at his business-made watch, standing on a business-made\Nsidewalk while he holds a business-made placard made out of business-made things.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.96,1:04:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, it's business. Well, okay. So now, when you croak, what are they going\Nto put you in? Because business makes caskets, too. You know what I'm saying? So we have
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.19,1:04:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to accept that and see business for what it is. The corporate culture, you know, is really\Nthe out-picturing of abundance. People talk about abundance. Well, here it is. Here we
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.53,1:04:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,are in this magnificent room, magnificent carpet, all kinds of electronic equipment.\NI got these books. I got these books. I got these books. I got these books. I got these
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.59,1:04:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,books. I got these books. I got these books. I got these books. I got these books. I got\Nthese books. I got these books. I got these books. I got these books. I got these books.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.65,1:05:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's sort of stupid to sit here and vilify business when my whole survival\Nfrom moment to moment is dependent on business, isn't it? Without business, there'd be
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.34,1:05:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,no electric. We would all be sitting here in the dark. You wouldn't hear any of my voice,\Nand none of us would have anything on.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.78,1:05:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So the alternative to that is to live in a cave and spin your own clothes. And if anybody\Nwants to try that lifestyle, you have the severe ascetic, I'll tell you, it's cold in
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.28,1:05:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,cold in winter and it's hot in summer. No. So, what industry and business represent is\Nthe collective enterprise. It's the collective abundance of all of us. The total business
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.38,1:05:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,output of America belongs to all of us. Now, technically, you may be only legally entitled\Nto this little piece of stock or whatever, but you get, we all get the benefit of the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.92,1:05:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,all of it. And to say, how much of it do I own, you're coming from the solar plexus\Nbecause you can all walk in here for free. It doesn't cost you anything to walk into
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.38,1:06:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,this hotel and walk around and go to the men's room and walk out on the sidewalk. All of\Nthat costs millions of dollars. So, from moment to moment, we all benefit by an infinite trillions
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.78,1:06:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of dollars of productive output of our society. So, when you vilify industry and business,\Nyou're vilifying yourself because that's your own energy pouring out there and that's
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.76,1:06:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of your survival. Without penicillin, you're going to be dead. Without a hospital\Nto go to when you have a heart attack, you're going to stop breathing and stay right there.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.28,1:06:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Without an ambulance to come and get you, without an oxygen tank. So, every single instant,\Nyou are benefi-, benefiting by the total output of the industriousness and integrity of the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.05,1:06:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,society.\NSo, we've inherited a certain momentum from our previous generation. So, the previous
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.15,1:07:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,generation already had Model A Fords, Model T Fords. We had a 29 Model A Ford Roadster\Nwith a rumble seat. It was fantastic, but it wasn't a streamliner. So, in the 30s, when
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.96,1:07:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the first streamliner car came out, and also the railroad, you know, we had the old locomotive.\NWell, then the streamliner, the Hiawatha came out.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.00,1:07:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And the train went by once a day, 4 o'clock. We lived on the sticks. So, we'd take our\Nbicycles and drive a couple of miles and we'd wait until 4 o'clock. And the Hiawatha would
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.76,1:07:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,come through. That was the high point of our day and then the, then it was gone.\NOkay. So, the hard work of all of us, generation after generation then, we collect a certain
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.15,1:07:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,amount of capital behind us. The accumulated infrastructure of our society, the amount\Nof money we make is a free gift. Sidewalks don't cost you anything. They're paid for
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.26,1:08:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,by your parents and your grandparents. The automobile industry has already worked itself\Nto death to produce the car that you just walk in. You can buy a better used one now
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.40,1:08:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,for practically nothing than you could buy brand new .\NSo, everyone benefits by the total collective output of all of us. Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.15,1:08:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,we should reauthenticate it, reappreciate it, and re-contextualize the value and building\NBut the importance of that to all of our survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.09,1:08:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We as a nation are enormously productive, and we are like a bastion, we're like a sign\Nto the rest of the world, this is what's possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.25,1:08:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what's possible.\NOf course, we say it arose according to a certain economic system, which we would like
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.35,1:08:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to see other people incorporate.\NI don't really care whether they incorporate our free enterprise system or not, what do
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.55,1:09:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I care about it, as long as I get penicillin when I'm sick and oxygen when I can't breathe\Nanymore and I've got a car to park, and a parking lot that somebody paid for, who paid
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.50,1:09:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,for all that pavement out there?\NSo you ride around all day on the back of corporate production and industry through
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.80,1:09:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,a number of generations.\NSo to vilify it is sort of stupid, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.89,1:09:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,To vilify it, okay.\NYou can vilify it and stigmatize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.93,1:09:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,By warping it, by projecting certain misinterpretations.\NThe image of the victim and the perpetrator is so inculcated in our disruptive society
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.39,1:09:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,right now, it's first of all very, it makes you sound very important to stigmatize something\Nand criticize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.92,1:10:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So if your self-esteem is not too high, what you do is you go about criticizing everything.\NThe government, state and federal.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.25,1:10:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The military, industry.\NFord Motor Company, you name it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.73,1:10:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Part of this criticism comes out of distortions of Marxism.\NThe distortions that see authority as authoritarian.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.15,1:10:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That see authority as exploitive.\NExploitation like any judgmental thing depends on your point of view.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.43,1:10:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Henry Ford introduced the first five dollar a day workplace.\NFive dollars a day.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.28,1:10:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It was overwhelming.\NThe downside of Henry Ford.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.21,1:10:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you weren't allowed to smile or go to the bathroom.\NYou got paid good money,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.64,1:10:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but you weren't supposed to have a good time at it.\NAnybody who joked around was the foreman quickly told you.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.10,1:10:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you wanted to go to the bathroom twice,\Nyou say you went already this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.14,1:11:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I worked in an automobile company, a factory,\Nand I remember how it was with the production line.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.85,1:11:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you can picture that production line any way you want to.\NSo you see, when we talk about the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.82,1:11:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,we're always talking about perceptions.\NWas that production line my road to freedom,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.10,1:11:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,or was it my road to captivity?\NDepends on your political prejudice in the matter.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.78,1:11:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It was my means of working my way through medical school\Nand therefore freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.82,1:11:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So the assembly line then was to me a road to freedom.\NYou could say, well, the assembly line
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.53,1:11:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is symbolic.\NIt's a symbolic of captivity.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.69,1:11:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the captive worker who's chained to his post,\Nand time did go very slowly,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.34,1:11:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,because this auto body would come down,\Ncreak, creak, creak, creak, creak, creak,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.03,1:11:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I was supposed to go bzzzt on it,\Nand then it went creak, creak, creak, creak,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.03,1:12:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,down to the next person.\NWell, you had to wait like 45 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.03,1:12:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you, that was the longest 45 seconds.\NI did my bzzzt, and I had nothing to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.03,1:12:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, nothing to do for 45 minutes.\NOh, my 45 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.03,1:12:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'd almost want to run over and grab that thing,\Nbut I'm here, you bastard.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.30,1:12:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Tedium.\NAll right, so instead of demonizing industry
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.69,1:12:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and business, et cetera,\Nlet's say we realize that you wouldn't even exist without it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.02,1:12:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Few of the people would be alive in this room\Nif it wasn't for industry or business.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.14,1:12:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Industry and business is what puts out pharmaceuticals.\NThat's why we don't have the plague anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.14,1:12:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's why we don't have tuberculosis anymore.\NWhen I was an intern,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.97,1:12:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,infantile paralysis was,\Nall these diseases were rampant,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.97,1:12:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,whooping cough and diphtheria and typhoid.\NWhat's that one where your arm went weak
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.97,1:12:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you were paralyzed?\NPresident Roosevelt had it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.48,1:13:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Polio, yes, polio.\NMy job then, I was the only doctor on
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.26,1:13:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in this infectious disease hospital.\NThe head doctor had an alcohol problem,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.26,1:13:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and he disappeared and left it for the intern.\NSo here I am, an intern,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.26,1:13:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,right in the middle of a polio epidemic,\Nand I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.26,1:13:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's no laboratory technician,\Nso the mother brings the child in.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.26,1:13:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tell from across the room,\Nhe's got polio.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.26,1:13:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see the one side out on the kid,\Nand I can see the terror in the parent's eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.26,1:13:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was by myself,\Nso I quickly ran in.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.27,1:13:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,First I was the doctor,\Nthen I was the lab technician.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.50,1:13:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I ran the back, and I did a spinal tap on this kid,\Nand I spun it down in the centrifuge,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.50,1:13:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and I counted, and I looked,\NI saw all the white cells there,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.43,1:13:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had to go out and tell the parents.\NThey would drop dead,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.97,1:14:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,just drop over on the floor,\Nand the father would bring us out
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.10,1:14:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was hopeless,\Nhopeless paralysis.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.47,1:14:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you got up to the thoracic region,\Nthe diaphragm, you went in an iron lung.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.89,1:14:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And life in an iron lung is not fun.\NYou lay on your back inside this iron thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.39,1:14:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can't breathe when you want to breathe.\NYou breathe when it breathes you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.32,1:14:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And boredom, talk about boredom,\Ntalk about 45 seconds waiting for the next auto body
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.32,1:14:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to come down.\NYou imagine spending years that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.32,1:14:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Industry and commerce has saved us from that.\NNone of us have to spend our life
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.32,1:14:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in an iron lung.\NIf you need oxygen, an ambulance will come
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.02,1:14:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and bring it to you.\NCarefully trained EMTs are experts.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.44,1:14:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I've watched some EMT teams work together.\NImpressive, I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.44,1:14:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like a ballet.\NEach one just moved like they were telepathically connected.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.53,1:14:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Magical.\NTo save your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.69,1:14:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we owe our life to industry.\NWe owe certain allegiance to it,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.69,1:15:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore we owe a certain\Nthankfulness, gratitude, and respect.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.69,1:15:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That off the backs of all these workers,\Nwe have
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.50,1:15:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the gift of our society.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.88,1:15:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I think\Nbusiness and industry needs to reinvent itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.22,1:15:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you why.\NBecause it has bought
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.22,1:15:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of the criticism against it.\NIt's incorporated the negative values.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.22,1:15:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It itself\Ncomes from guilt and apology all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.48,1:15:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Please forgive us.\NAn apologetic,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.60,1:15:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,defensive, guilt-ridden,\Nshame-based kind of
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.60,1:15:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of, really,\Nthe distortions of reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.05,1:15:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're integrous, and you've done the best\Nyou can, and you know your company's doing
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.05,1:15:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the best you can, you can look everybody in the eye\Nand you don't have to give an apology
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.05,1:15:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,for anything. You can give an explanation,\Nbut you don't need to give any apologies.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.05,1:16:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to apologize\Nfor. What they're usually
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.34,1:16:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,hit with is the distortion of truth,\Nand now they have to apologize, not for
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.34,1:16:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,reality, but for some distortion of truth.\NIt's like, when did you
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.34,1:16:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,quit beating your wife, you know what I mean?\NWell, he never did beat his wife.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.01,1:16:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, the most powerful nation\Non Earth came about as a result of
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.80,1:16:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the free enterprise system,\Nof which enterprise industry
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.82,1:16:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and business,\Nand I'll get into
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.76,1:16:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,some of these examples.\NSo all the people who denigrate
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.35,1:16:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,our form of life,\Nhate capitalism, hate the free market system,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.35,1:16:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,hate the presidency,\Nhate all that, I notice that
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.35,1:16:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't move.\NSo, why
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.89,1:16:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,are you still here, freako?\NIf you don't like Gonsaville,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.98,1:16:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,why are you still living in Gonsaville?\NBecause the positive payoff
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.38,1:16:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of living in America is so tremendous\Nthat people are willing to die to get here,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.38,1:17:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and they cross the Mexican border,\Nthey die by the hundreds every year,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.47,1:17:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to get to the land of free enterprise,\Nwhich everybody else ungratefully
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.47,1:17:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and non-integrously\Nis busy attacking and trying to
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.47,1:17:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,denigrate.\NMy feeling is that business
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.85,1:17:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and industry should recontextualize\Nitself to itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.85,1:17:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't even realize to\Nthemselves who they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.43,1:17:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody has to tell them.\NWithout you, practically everybody in this room
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.43,1:17:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,would be dead.\NBefore the days of industry, the average age of death
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.02,1:17:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,was like 45 or something.\NBecause there was nothing to keep you alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.98,1:17:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There were no pharmaceuticals, there were no\Ndiagnostic, there was no x-rays,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.98,1:17:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there was no bacteriologic laboratories,\Nthere was no hospitals.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.92,1:17:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Without industry, just about everybody\Nwould be dead, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.92,1:17:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The death rate in childbirth\Namongst women was a third.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.88,1:18:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,A third of women died in childbirth\Ndue to puerperal fever.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.93,1:18:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There were no antibiotics,\Nno sterilization procedures.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.46,1:18:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So the medical industry then came forth\Nwith all ways to save
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.61,1:18:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,human life from suffering\Nas well as disfigurement
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.61,1:18:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and death.\NThe average healthy, reasonable
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.68,1:18:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,human being lives to be\Nwhat, 80 now?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.68,1:18:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWhen I grew up, 65 you retired
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.67,1:18:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and at 66 or 67\Nyou had your heart attack
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.67,1:18:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was goodbye.\NThat's true, everybody retired at 65
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.89,1:18:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and they had a heart attack within the first few years.\NThe average age of death
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.89,1:18:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,was around 67, 68.\NI would have been dead 10 years already
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.22,1:18:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and more.\NTo respect then
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.10,1:18:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the American public should respect\Nthe very source of its own affluence
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.10,1:19:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of trying to attack it\Nand denigrate it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.35,1:19:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,To do this, corporate America has to\Nunderstand its own value to the world
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.35,1:19:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and to each other.\NSo we need to recontextualize
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.73,1:19:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the value of human life\Nas it expresses itself
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.73,1:19:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in business and commerce\Nwhich is, after all,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.73,1:19:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,at least eight hours of most people's day\Nfive days a week
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.73,1:19:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you're in that world.\NIn the world that you denigrate and hate
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.73,1:19:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,your life is going to be miserable.\NSo we have to value
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.14,1:19:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the value of our own work\Nthe value of that business
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.14,1:19:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to society.\NSo I say we need to recontextualize
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.59,1:19:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the significance of corporate America\Nto itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.55,1:19:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,To do that, you have to first of all\Nlook more at the context
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.55,1:19:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,than the content.\NA lot of times business makes
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.06,1:19:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,actually horrendous mistakes\Ncoming out of this apologist, defensive attitude
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.06,1:20:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,partly due to the trial lawyers association\Nand various other things.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.06,1:20:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But, hmm\NI've watched a lot of really painful disasters
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.18,1:20:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore I always recommend\Nfirst understand who you really are to the world
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.18,1:20:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and stop being apologetic.\NStop being guilt ridden
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.50,1:20:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because you make profits.\NWho gets the profits of business?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.85,1:20:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The country gets the profits of business.\NIf I'm a multi-billionaire
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.77,1:20:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't put it in a coffee can\Nin my backyard
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.77,1:20:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I put it in some industry.\NI put it in a bank.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.31,1:20:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And that capital goes back out into the world\Nto be
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.47,1:20:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,of use for making\Nbuilding universities and things.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.47,1:20:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,When you get old and guilty\Nyou can start a society
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.47,1:20:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,a beneficial society\Nbut during
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.59,1:20:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,our lifetime\Ndoes anybody keep their money in the mattress here?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.59,1:21:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody hide it in the mattress?\NAll your dirty capital
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.10,1:21:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've accumulated\Nyou rotten capitalists
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.10,1:21:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you keep it in a coffee can in the backyard.\NAnybody here keep your money
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.10,1:21:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in a coffee can in the backyard?\NNobody.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.10,1:21:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody keep it under the mattress?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.55,1:21:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody chop it up and flush it down the toilet?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.77,1:21:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so the money goes right back\Nit flows right back out.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.77,1:21:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nominally yours, nominally.\NFunctionally it's not yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.10,1:21:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you put it in the bank\Nit's really the bank's isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.10,1:21:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The bank decides what it's going to do with it.\NHere where I live
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.10,1:21:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,they're going to start a new 125\Nhouse development project.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.10,1:21:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's going to cost millions and millions of dollars.\NThey've got to run water, basic things,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.10,1:21:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,electric, all that.\NSo what we need is
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.42,1:21:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,a consciousness coach.\NNow the word coach is sort of over abused
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.42,1:22:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in business and all.\NSo we need a better word than consciousness coach
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.42,1:22:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but frankly that's what they need.\NSomebody to re-contextualize back
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.47,1:22:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,first of all to the company\Nas a whole
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.47,1:22:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,with the executives and the people\Nthat interface with the public.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.47,1:22:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't mean public relations people\Nbecause they're a lot of times idiots.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.47,1:22:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They're worse than anything.\NThey're a lot in their 20s and they're abrasive.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.73,1:22:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They put out advertisements\Nthat make you disgusted.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.73,1:22:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That cracking duck.\NIf you don't shut up that cracking duck.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.02,1:22:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate Affleck.\NI really hate Affleck.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.25,1:22:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now there's a guy, a new TV commercial\Nthis guy can't get his computer to work
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.25,1:22:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,so he screams at you.\NBut the sound of screaming
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.38,1:22:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,if you calibrate the sound of screaming\Nit's way down low.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.27,1:22:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Loud cracking ducks it's way down low.\NAffleck I telepathically communicated
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.06,1:23:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,with Affleck and I said\Noh god this is awful fellas.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.57,1:23:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I really did sort of hold a\Ncorrective view of the duck.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.98,1:23:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I do notice that\Nthe duck now comes on
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.98,1:23:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's much quieter.\NYou can get more customers
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.46,1:23:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,with a happy quiet duck\Nthan an abrasive one.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.22,1:23:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Affleck was coming to\Nthe girls ranch where I'm at
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.22,1:23:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're providing the health insurance\Nand I said I don't want to see the guy
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.72,1:23:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,when he comes here.\NI said I hate Affleck.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.97,1:23:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm talking about more seriously\Nis the awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.18,1:23:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you see they get backed up against the corner\Nand they come out of guilt
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.18,1:23:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they start using deception.\NAnd what we found out with consciousness research
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.53,1:23:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is\Nwe have permission to ask this
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.27,1:24:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in front of this crowd.\NUnconsciously everybody knows
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.00,1:24:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,when they're being lied to.\NUnconsciously everybody knows
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.67,1:24:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,when they're being lied to.\NConsequently
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.67,1:24:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the company executive\Nthe CEO gets on TV
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.64,1:24:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and then stonewalls\Nand flatly lies
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.64,1:24:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is fooling nobody at all.\NSo this recalls a couple of
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.06,1:24:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,painful interviews.\NIn as much as that which is
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.47,1:24:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,like defeat on plump juicy\Ninnocent things
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.18,1:24:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,we can say that a successful corporation\Nautomatically draws to itself enemies
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.18,1:24:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of its success\Nout of envy and sheer hatred
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.18,1:24:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,for that which is integrous.\NSo Sam Walton and I
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.44,1:24:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,used to correspond and of course I calibrated\Nhis principles and we calibrated Walmart
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.44,1:24:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that. And as we said last time\Nwe predicted in 95 what would be
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.44,1:25:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and sure enough Walmart turned out to be\Nthe biggest corporation in America
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.44,1:25:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,built on integrous principles.\NProof that integrity pays on the bottom line.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.47,1:25:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well Sam Walton died\Nand Walmart calibrated
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.97,1:25:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,around 380 I think when\Nhe was alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.97,1:25:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's dropped to maybe 15 or 20 points since then\Nbecause anyway
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.27,1:25:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the next president came up was black\Nand I watched the most painful interview on TV.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.27,1:25:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time those who like\Nto attack big business and find something wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.56,1:25:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,were attacking Walmart\Nthat they were employing child labor
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.56,1:25:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in third world countries.\NThey were like the dirty old
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.56,1:25:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,men thriving off\Nthese poor little children's
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.19,1:25:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,work and sweat and labor.\NOh boy, oh boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.19,1:25:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So Black gets up there\Nand he defends himself
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.26,1:25:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and sort of\Nflat out, oh we don't do that
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.00,1:25:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,or some idiot like that.\NThat was really painful
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.92,1:26:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because I thought you know I wish I had a chance\Nto talk to this executive before he got up there
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.92,1:26:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because you look at the evolution\Nof an industrial society.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.97,1:26:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Third world countries are not industrialized yet.\NThey're coming out of agrarian.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.14,1:26:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we came out of agrarian in America\Nwe went through the sweatshop phase.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.14,1:26:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody does.\NThe children in the needlework, the seamstresses
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.27,1:26:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you remember the one in Boston\Nthe seamstresses were all in New York City.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.27,1:26:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They were locked into their\Nfactory
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.30,1:26:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,with the sewing machines and they all burned to death.\NRemember that?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.30,1:26:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you come out of an agrarian society\Nyou go through that phase of child labor
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.30,1:26:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,women laborers\Nseamstresses
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.39,1:26:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and sort of as you move into industrialization\Nso you have a phase there.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.39,1:26:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now people don't realize\Nwhat poverty is
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.77,1:26:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and you look at some of the favelas\Non the sides of the mountains
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.84,1:26:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in Brazil\Nwhat's the big city in Brazil?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.69,1:27:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Rio.\NYou visit those shacks on the side of the mountain
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.69,1:27:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and you realize what poverty is.\NNow if those children
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.77,1:27:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,could get a job at 10 cents an hour\Nthe whole family's economy
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.77,1:27:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,would jump like this.\NThey could support the whole family.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.77,1:27:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So in a third world country\Nyou have a need for needle trades
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.89,1:27:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the children are available\Nbecause that's their phase
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.34,1:27:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of an agrarian society.\NAlright so to support
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.75,1:27:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution of a third world country\Ninto an industrialized society
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.75,1:27:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,if American capital\Nlike let's say Walmart
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.90,1:27:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,goes to a country like that\Nand says look we'll give you
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.90,1:27:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,what to them is huge amounts of money\Nto do this
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.22,1:27:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and needle work\Nin return for which
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.22,1:27:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we want the children's work hours\Nlimited to 8 hours
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.22,1:27:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to have fresh air\Nthey must still have medical coverage
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.22,1:27:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,every child must have at least 2 hours a day of school\Nyou're in a bargaining position
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.22,1:28:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you're holding the big bucks\Nand they want your big bucks
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.22,1:28:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can trade business\Nfor humanitarian principles
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.30,1:28:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you understand?\NSo Walmart could be the liberator
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.30,1:28:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of these exploited third world children\Nthey brought the whole culture up
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.30,1:28:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to abundance\Nthe respect for human life
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.35,1:28:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that no door should be locked\Nwith children in there
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.35,1:28:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in case of fire etc\Nso they could have been the hero
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.35,1:28:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,they could have been the savior\Nof the beneficial savior
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.35,1:28:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of the exploited\Nthird world children
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.35,1:28:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,instead they came on\Nand stonewalled it
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.86,1:28:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,what happened to our explanations\Nthe Red Cross
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.89,1:28:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,did the same thing\NNew Coke did the same thing
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.89,1:28:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Coca Cola Company with the New Coke\Nthe bald dead disaster
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.89,1:28:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,all these are\Nblatant examples of
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.89,1:29:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,not being able to contextualize\Nthe thing in such a way
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.89,1:29:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's coming from\Nguilt and lying
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.89,1:29:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,which we just demonstrated\Nthis morning
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.89,1:29:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody knows when they're being lied to\Nso you come out rotten
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.89,1:29:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you come out rotten instead of a savior\Nand now you vindicate
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.89,1:29:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the vilification of industry\Nbecause you've just been
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.89,1:29:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,industry at its worst\Nwhere's our piggy
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.46,1:29:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,there you have\NAmerican capitalism
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.46,1:29:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,as viewed from the Marxist position\Nexploiting the worker
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.46,1:29:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,workers you have nothing to lose\Nbut your chains
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.85,1:29:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and what is the fate of the worker\Nin Russia, China
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.69,1:29:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,all the communist countries\Nok
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.80,1:29:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,there you got the downside\Nof capitalism
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.80,1:30:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you exploit her\Nok
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.11,1:30:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,so a coach would\Ncoach people on how to recontextualize
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.11,1:30:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,he would coach you on timing\Nthis week American Airlines
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.78,1:30:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,after the union\Nsettled the contract
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.94,1:30:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,then tells you that the top executives\Nare about to get 1.5 million bonuses
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.94,1:30:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that are exempt from\Nwhat timing huh
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.94,1:30:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,what timing you don't need enemies\Nwhen you do that against yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.94,1:30:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\NI mean stupid I mean really
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.94,1:30:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,even they realize it was really\Ndumb dumb dumb and they've retracted it
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.94,1:30:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but the bad news you know\Nthe bad image is out there already
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.94,1:30:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,so there's Mr. Pig out there\Nrunning American Airlines
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.94,1:30:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,now we'll leave Mr. Pig out hidden away\Nok
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.56,1:30:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so to recontextualize the thing\Nfirst of all you got to come from truth
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.56,1:30:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to have integrity\Neverybody knows when you're speaking the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.56,1:31:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can come out as a big company\Nand say you know that was a bad mistake
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.72,1:31:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and we learned from it\Nnobody holds you that's against you
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.72,1:31:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you hear anybody\Ncriticizing any past business mistakes
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.90,1:31:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that the businesses came out and said\Nwell you goofed on that one
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.90,1:31:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,no because when somebody admits the truth\Nyou're willing to forgive them
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.90,1:31:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,when they stand there in stonewall\Nand frankly lie on your face
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.90,1:31:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you lose your respect for them\Nok so we want to integrate
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.90,1:31:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,business into the overall human\Ncommunity
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.90,1:31:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of setting it aside\Nwhere it's vulnerable to attack and criticism
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.47,1:31:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,ok\Nthere is a thing I wrote about
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.47,1:31:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in power versus force\Ncalled critical factor analysis
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.09,1:31:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,we haven't spoken about\Ncalibrating the levels of truth
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.09,1:31:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in the various aspects of business\Nbut you can calibrate the level of any corporation
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.09,1:31:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,every department in that corporation\Nall the key positions
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.11,1:32:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you can ask\Nthe correct calibration
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.11,1:32:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and all this job is blank\Nso you've got to find somebody that has that
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.85,1:32:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of hiring somebody that doesn't have it\Nand then firing because they don't have it
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.97,1:32:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,well you shouldn't hire them if they don't have it\Nwe said this morning
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.97,1:32:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the perfect calibration for a presidency\Nof the United States of America
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.97,1:32:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is 460 that's perfect\Nif you ask the question
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.97,1:32:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the most perfect calibration to fulfill\Nthe duties of that job you get 460
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.93,1:32:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,people would say wasn't 510 better\Nno 510 is not better
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.03,1:32:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,people would say it's all idiotic\Nwe're not interested in politics
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.03,1:32:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,who cares about that\N420 wouldn't be able to have the moxie
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.18,1:32:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to grab the complexity of the overall situation\Nso
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.64,1:32:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,alright you can calibrate every aspect of business\Nand
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.77,1:32:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,show its application to research\Nmarketing, advertising, production
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.06,1:33:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a thing called critical factor analysis\Nwhich I mentioned in power versus force
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.06,1:33:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,most of these corporate interactions\Nare with multiple corporations
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.06,1:33:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,interacting here with the government\Nhere with the public, here with sales
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.06,1:33:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,here with marketing, public image, publicity\Nit's highly complex
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.14,1:33:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so how can you tell where\Nan alteration
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.53,1:33:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,can change the whole thing\Nin critical factor analysis
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.89,1:33:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,means in a non-linear\Nbecause now we're out of the linear
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.89,1:33:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and into the non-linear\Nthe complexity is already out of the linear
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.89,1:33:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond the capacity of a computer to figure out\Nthe multiplicity of factors
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.89,1:33:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,now run into the millions\Nhow can you find out where in those millions
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.42,1:33:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and millions of factors\Nmost of which you can't even get on a computer
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.42,1:33:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because a large percentage\Nof them are coming out of the unconscious
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.48,1:33:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore not available\Nto put into a computer
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.81,1:33:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,how can you tell where can we\Ntouch this complex interaction
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.81,1:34:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and bring about a desired result\Nthe example
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.73,1:34:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I used in the book was a huge locomotive\Ncarrying billions of
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.73,1:34:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,pounds of\Nfreight behind it
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.05,1:34:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,15 freight cars\Na mass, a huge staggering mass
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.05,1:34:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and a very complex\Npowerful engine, let's say
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.05,1:34:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,two or three diesel engines\Nwe've seen them go by out here in Arizona
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.14,1:34:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,through the Navajo lands\Netc. with three locomotives
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.23,1:34:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and a mile and a half\Nof freight cars
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.17,1:34:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,do you know you can stop that whole thing\Nwith one finger like this
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.30,1:34:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,all you have to do is know where to\Ntouch the control and this entire
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.30,1:34:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,thing comes to a stop\None light little touch
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.02,1:34:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,less than half an ounce can stop\Nthis entire monster
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.02,1:34:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,get in its tracks\Nthat's the critical point
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.93,1:35:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the critical factor analysis\Nif you know where to put just a half an ounce of
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.93,1:35:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,pressure the whole system\Nchanges
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.14,1:35:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,so it isn't a complex thing\Na slight shift of image
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.85,1:35:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and your entire company and its impact\Nand the response to society totally changes
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.85,1:35:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,just the slightest\Nimplication
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.36,1:35:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you are coming from good will\Nrather than greed already impacts
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.36,1:35:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,people quite considerably\Nthat you're concerned
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.50,1:35:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,this is different than advertising\Nadvertising to me is made up by
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.50,1:35:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,young people with insufficient wisdom\Nto be able to contextualize the advertising
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.50,1:35:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it has any impact\Nif you calibrate a lot of
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.59,1:35:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean the companies spend\Nenormous amounts of money on this trash advertising
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.59,1:35:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you can tell it came out of\Na 24 year old's idea
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.65,1:35:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of what would be cute or smart\Nand it's losing 90% of the audience
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.75,1:35:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because first of all\Nthey presume everybody out there
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.75,1:35:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is 22 years old and grew up with computers\Nso the average commercial
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.75,1:36:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,was like this\Nand I say to Susan
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.86,1:36:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,what are they advertising\Nhow many times have I said that to you
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.38,1:36:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I said what is it they're advertising\Nit was a cute frog and then a locomotive
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.38,1:36:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and then somebody stabbing somebody\Nand then some rock music and then all these flashing lights
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.38,1:36:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's gone\NI was trying to catch the label who made it
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.38,1:36:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,what is it\Nthere's one that says
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.78,1:36:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't actually even make anything\Nwe only improve things
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.26,1:36:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so why are they wasting their money on me\Nif they improve tennis shoes
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.82,1:36:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but don't sell tennis shoes\Nthen they should be advertising to manufacturers
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.82,1:36:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to use their product\Nto improve their tennis shoes
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.82,1:36:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and why am I sitting through their commercial\Nwe don't make tennis balls
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.02,1:36:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we make them better\Nthat's good for them
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.21,1:36:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,pointless advertising\Nthe speed of processing information
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.71,1:37:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we see commercials\Nthat really grab you in the heart
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.71,1:37:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,there are some commercials that are stunning\Nstunningly brilliant
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.71,1:37:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,stunningly poignant\Nleave a lasting message
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.77,1:37:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and totally change your image of that company\Nand how you feel about it
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.02,1:37:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,so American products don't belong to companies\Nthey belong to America
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.02,1:37:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,when you recontextualize who you are\Nbusiness and corporate America
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.02,1:37:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you are America\Ntherefore the lack of respect
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.38,1:37:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,for the company's symbols\Nto me is also outrageous
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.38,1:37:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and obviously done by 24 year olds\Nlog cabin syrup is supposed to be
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.60,1:37:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in a tin log cabinet\NAunt Jemima's pancakes
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.31,1:37:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is supposed to be a nice chunky dark lady\NI don't want to see some slim blonde
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.10,1:37:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,because she's been modernized to modern America\Nthose things
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.10,1:37:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,those symbols have become sacred to us\NNew Coke found that out
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.39,1:37:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you mess with us and you got trouble\Nso America is saying
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.39,1:38:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you mess with us and you got big trouble\Npeople hate the new Coke
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.15,1:38:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't buy it\Nthese people do bad enough
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.80,1:38:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,they keep changing the\Nat least they stay with red white and blue
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.80,1:38:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but I just get used to Pepsi this way\Nand then they turn it this way
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.18,1:38:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean why are they doing that\Nso if business views itself
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.02,1:38:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,as semi-sacred to the public\Nwe hold these things in a semi-sacred way
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.18,1:38:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I still long for the Burma shave sign\Nlittle shavers take it easy
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.75,1:38:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,your driving is driving me crazy\Nsomething like that
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.75,1:39:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the Burma shave sign\NI've never cared for that president's wife
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.75,1:39:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,who took down all the roadsides\Nin the image of beauty
Dialogue: 0,1:39:06.75,1:39:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,this is somebody rather\Nwell she was a do-gooder of some kind
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.68,1:39:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,now you got to look at boring miles\Nof nothingness or apartment buildings
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.44,1:39:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,or something\Nwe used to have a big sign
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.44,1:39:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,a Janssen lady swimming suit\Nthirty foot long
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.82,1:39:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,yellow swimming suit\Nlife is exciting
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.34,1:39:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,well let's see\Nintegrity show itself in business
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.73,1:39:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,first of all we know that goodwill\Nis an energy
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.73,1:39:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it's an energy\Nthey either got it or they ain't
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.52,1:39:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't fake it\Ngoodwill and good intention
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.85,1:39:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,it then spills out into the workforce\Nso that the workforce now
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.85,1:39:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to represent\Nwho they are via their work
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.10,1:40:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so\Nwe
Dialogue: 0,1:40:04.00,1:40:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,using critical factor analysis\Nwe show that
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.00,1:40:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,these principles\Nresults in
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.38,1:40:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,benefit everywhere\Nlower
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.89,1:40:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,sick time off the job\Nlower employee turnover
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.93,1:40:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,greater productivity\Nwhy because
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.93,1:40:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to believe\Nyour product and your company
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.93,1:40:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,has to have integrity\Nfor you to put forth your best
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.11,1:40:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're just punching a time clock\Nthat's perfunctory
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.11,1:40:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and that may calibrate at 2.02\Nis sort of the IRS
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.30,1:40:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,they do it but\Nyou're not happy to see from them
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.14,1:40:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not happy to see them\Nthey're not happy
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.14,1:40:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,when you learn from the IRS\Nyou don't feel cheered up about it
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.30,1:40:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,congratulations we appreciate\Nthe fact that you have now sent us
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.30,1:41:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,an accurate tax return\Nfor 35 years doctor
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.31,1:41:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,one time I got one of those\Ntaxpayer compliance dragnet deals
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.31,1:41:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,this is some years ago\Nin which they take a certain category
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.31,1:41:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody gets audited in that category\Nthe computer picked them out by
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.81,1:41:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,somehow so I mean\Nyou know this was draconian and I had to
Dialogue: 0,1:41:21.81,1:41:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,pull out a receipt for every time\NI went to the bathroom and prove every gallon
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.81,1:41:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of gas so it was a lot of work\Nyou know it took a week or two to get all this crap
Dialogue: 0,1:41:29.81,1:41:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,together and\Nwhen he got through he found that it was
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.85,1:41:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,perfect so he gave you a letter\Nthat you had
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.85,1:41:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,showed 100% perfect\Ncompliance that's the only good
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.26,1:41:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,news I ever got from those people\Nyou're a good guy
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.06,1:41:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you're ok\Nthe next year would you know
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.25,1:41:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,out of sheer chance the computer\Npicked me out again so I got one of those
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.25,1:42:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,taxpayer compliance audits\Ntwo years in a row
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.25,1:42:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,ok\Nso the way it went was I knew he was
Dialogue: 0,1:42:05.72,1:42:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,coming so I laid everything\Nout like you would for a king
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.78,1:42:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,he's the IRS guy\NI had everything laid out categorized
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.78,1:42:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I bought special folders for each thing\Nand I scheduled
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.92,1:42:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it being shrewd at the same time\Nnot stupid I scheduled it
Dialogue: 0,1:42:21.92,1:42:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,for a Friday afternoon\NI know Friday at 5 they're due back at the office
Dialogue: 0,1:42:27.84,1:42:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so we scheduled it for\N2.30 on a Friday afternoon
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.06,1:42:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,which means he would get his butt in and out\Nso facilitate
Dialogue: 0,1:42:36.06,1:42:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,his work so the way to be\Nsuccessful is to make other people
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.06,1:42:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,a success so what I did is I laid\Nit out that it would be a snap for him
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.06,1:42:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,easy\Nany anxieties or worries that he might
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.06,1:42:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,have I documented it\Nso his afternoon was
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.06,1:42:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,a snap and he left in an hour\Nand a half and I got another taxpayer compliance
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.42,1:43:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,letter and my life was a snap\Nso you see how
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.42,1:43:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,supporting each other pays back I supported\Nhis job his integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.42,1:43:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I made sure that when he went back\Nhe was bringing back
Dialogue: 0,1:43:08.42,1:43:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,truth and he saw\Nto it that I got acknowledgement for the hard
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.44,1:43:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,work I tried to make his\Nwork easy you understand so
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.44,1:43:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,how business works so\Nthe more we work to make our supply
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.44,1:43:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,as business\Na success the more ours is a success
Dialogue: 0,1:43:24.44,1:43:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,so success\Nthen feeds on itself people say
Dialogue: 0,1:43:28.89,1:43:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,how do you get success in this world\Nand there's many many a workshop
Dialogue: 0,1:43:32.89,1:43:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,on it and I certainly don't want to\Npretend to have any
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.89,1:43:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,knowledge of the subject I\Njust know experientially
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.09,1:43:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that if you put out\Nexcellence if you put out the best possible
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.09,1:43:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,can job you can do\Nno matter what it is
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.09,1:43:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the benefits of this world come to you\Nautomatically not in a linear fashion
Dialogue: 0,1:43:53.09,1:43:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not because you do this\Nthat you get that but you
Dialogue: 0,1:43:57.09,1:44:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,create a field and the field brings\Nyou abundance I used to
Dialogue: 0,1:44:02.88,1:44:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,lecture all over the place all over\Ntravel all over and
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.22,1:44:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,people would say well aren't you\Ngoing to charge for that and I
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.77,1:44:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,said I never charge for lecture well you're not\Nno because
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.96,1:44:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you're\Nexplaining to an interested audience
Dialogue: 0,1:44:20.96,1:44:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the most advanced knowledge on a subject\Navailable on the planet and
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.25,1:44:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,consequently their families\Nand their relatives and
Dialogue: 0,1:44:29.25,1:44:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,cities they came from\Nwould call up and want to refer their patients
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.27,1:44:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in see in other words the field\Nbrought in patients I don't have to advertise for patients
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.27,1:44:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in those days\Nthe way you built your practice was through
Dialogue: 0,1:44:41.60,1:44:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity the best possible\Nservice
Dialogue: 0,1:44:45.85,1:44:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the most perfect way you could be\Nand that creates a field
Dialogue: 0,1:44:49.85,1:44:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the field built\Nyour practice or not
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.43,1:44:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,nowadays doctors advertise I mean if I\Nhad to advertise for a patient
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.56,1:45:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,please give me a break\NI saw you because I read your ad in the
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.93,1:45:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,yellow pages alright\Nso then integrity then is its
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.02,1:45:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,own self reward let's see\Nalright so we can go through a company
Dialogue: 0,1:45:21.31,1:45:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,we can calibrate the energy\Nfield of all the departments whether people
Dialogue: 0,1:45:25.31,1:45:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,are fitting that department\Nyou see that employees build
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.31,1:45:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,your image in the world\Nand what we're talking about here is
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.76,1:45:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,context now\Nthe unenlightened person the
Dialogue: 0,1:45:37.76,1:45:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,less evolved person\Nis only concerned with content
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.76,1:45:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,not concerned with context\Ndo we understand
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.76,1:45:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,context\Ndo we
Dialogue: 0,1:45:50.18,1:45:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody might be lying out there\Ngive me this thing here
Dialogue: 0,1:45:56.10,1:46:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just going to dive in I got my water wings on\Nok we'll put it up here
Dialogue: 0,1:46:00.28,1:46:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,it's critical to\Nunderstand all spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.47,1:46:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,especially spiritual reality\Nand truth
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.77,1:46:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you see\Nthere is the content
Dialogue: 0,1:46:12.89,1:46:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,this is specific\Nthis is called the world of form
Dialogue: 0,1:46:17.06,1:46:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,see\Nthis is the world of form
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.40,1:46:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the world of the ego this is that\Nand therefore that's wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:46:25.40,1:46:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but this world\Nwhich is there
Dialogue: 0,1:46:29.47,1:46:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is within a field\Nyeah
Dialogue: 0,1:46:36.73,1:46:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,what the uninformed\Nand what science doesn't understand
Dialogue: 0,1:46:41.22,1:46:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is that\Nthe power of this is completely dependent
Dialogue: 0,1:46:45.34,1:46:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,on the field\Nthe truth of this
Dialogue: 0,1:46:49.78,1:46:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is completely dependent upon the field\Nwithout the field
Dialogue: 0,1:46:54.75,1:46:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,this has no meaning\Nit's the field that gives it meaning
Dialogue: 0,1:46:59.89,1:47:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so\Nif you think you're just going and punching a time clock
Dialogue: 0,1:47:04.35,1:47:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not getting much reward\Nyou get a paycheck
Dialogue: 0,1:47:08.35,1:47:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so big deal\Nyou can get a paycheck in any company
Dialogue: 0,1:47:12.35,1:47:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I can walk down any city street\Nat the height of unemployment
Dialogue: 0,1:47:16.35,1:47:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the headlines are screaming\NI can walk down any street
Dialogue: 0,1:47:20.77,1:47:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere in America\Nand within a block get a job
Dialogue: 0,1:47:24.77,1:47:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've done it over and over\Nat the height of unemployment
Dialogue: 0,1:47:28.77,1:47:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no such thing as unemployment\Nwhen unemployment is going on
Dialogue: 0,1:47:33.25,1:47:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you open the daily newspaper\Nand there's 14 pages of jobs
Dialogue: 0,1:47:37.25,1:47:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you mean where's the unemployment\Nthere's 14 pages of jobs here
Dialogue: 0,1:47:42.10,1:47:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,what you mean is you don't want to do that\Noh that's different okay
Dialogue: 0,1:47:46.23,1:47:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,oh you don't want to work\Nokay
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.50,1:47:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're willing there's always a job\Nbecause if there's no formal jobs
Dialogue: 0,1:47:54.50,1:47:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you create one\Nso in school I'd go down the street
Dialogue: 0,1:47:59.03,1:48:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't have a nickel for coffee\Nliterally in those days
Dialogue: 0,1:48:03.14,1:48:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the kids from college hung out\Nin the coffee house you had to have nickels
Dialogue: 0,1:48:07.14,1:48:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,so I'd go down the block from the college\Nstate teachers college
Dialogue: 0,1:48:11.77,1:48:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and knock on doors\Nand sooner or later somebody would want their windows washed
Dialogue: 0,1:48:15.77,1:48:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'd wash their windows for 50 cents an hour\Nor whatever it is
Dialogue: 0,1:48:19.77,1:48:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'd have the money to go back to the\Njob yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:48:23.77,1:48:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,so that comes out of willingness\Nso the willingness then was the power
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.02,1:48:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,this is a critical thing to understand\Nbecause this is what science doesn't understand
Dialogue: 0,1:48:34.02,1:48:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,see this is where Newtonian science stops right here\Nthen quantum mechanics starts to tickle you to go out there
Dialogue: 0,1:48:42.05,1:48:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is the world of non-linear dynamics\Nthis is the world of the linear Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:48:48.77,1:48:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is the world of spiritual reality\Nokay
Dialogue: 0,1:48:56.57,1:49:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,power is coming from the field\Nthis is the source of your power
Dialogue: 0,1:49:00.80,1:49:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the unenlightened person thinks\Nif I just strive harder
Dialogue: 0,1:49:04.80,1:49:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll make more money\NI'll work harder longer
Dialogue: 0,1:49:08.80,1:49:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,spend more money on advertising\Ncut down my employees wages
Dialogue: 0,1:49:14.14,1:49:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,push the envelope as hard as I can\Nthat's looking at it from causality
Dialogue: 0,1:49:18.68,1:49:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,if I push harder here\NI'll win more there
Dialogue: 0,1:49:22.68,1:49:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm too lazy to do that\NI mean
Dialogue: 0,1:49:27.89,1:49:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd rather be good at winning\Nwhat I do
Dialogue: 0,1:49:31.89,1:49:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and let them come to me\Nwhy should I push for customers
Dialogue: 0,1:49:36.51,1:49:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,so context brings you effortlessly\Nwhat you cannot achieve with effort
